	{ type = 'section_heading', text = 'Who should participate' },
	{ type = 'paragraph', text = 'PDPS welcomes submissions from researchers, practitioners, and policy experts working on privacy, data protection, surveillance, and related governance issues. Early-stage work and interdisciplinary perspectives are encouraged.' },
	{ type = 'two_column', left_title = 'Propose a talk', left_body = 'Send a short abstract that explains your question, method, and the discussion you want to have with the audience. Include your preferred format and any accessibility needs.', right_title = 'Archival submission', right_body = "**Call for archival submissions**\n\nEach edition publishes a call for submissions with scope, deadlines, and the OpenReview submission link. We welcome research talks, work-in-progress ideas, and practice-facing case studies.\n\n**Submissions & review (OpenReview)**\n\nSubmissions and reviews are managed in OpenReview. The call for submissions will include the venue link and required fields.\n\n**Proceedings (CEUR-WS)**\n\nAccepted papers are planned for an open-access CEUR-WS proceedings volume. CEUR-WS publishes new volumes under CC BY 4.0, and camera-ready papers will use the CEURART template (LaTeX/Overleaf) shared in the final call.\n\n**Important dates (TBA)**\n\n- Call for submissions opens: TBA\n- Submission deadline: TBA\n- Notifications: TBA\n- Camera-ready: TBA" },
	{ type = 'section_heading', text = 'Registration' },
	{ type = 'paragraph', text = 'Registration details are announced with each new edition. When registration is required, the 2026 edition page links to the relevant form and participation instructions.' },
	{ type = 'button_row', items = [
